zi Persecution and Murder of the Jews |date=2010 |publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|location=Oxford |isbn=978-0-19-280436-5 |language=en |ref=harv}}\n:{{cite book |last1=Lorman |first1=Thomas |title=The Making of the Slovak People's Party: Religion, Nationalism and the Culture War in Early 20th-Century Europe |date=2019 |publisher=[[Bloomsbury Publishing]] |location=London |isbn=978-1-350-10938-4 |language=en|ref=harv}}\n:{{cite book |last1=Silberklang |first1=David |title=Gates of Tears: the Holocaust in the Lublin District |date=2013 |publisher=[[Yad Vashem]] |location=Jerusalem |isbn=978-965-308-464-3 |language=English|title-link=Gates of Tears: the Holocaust in the Lublin District |ref=harv}}\n:{{cite book |last1=\u0160indel\u00e1\u0159ov\u00e1 |first1=Lenka |title=Finale der Vernichtung: die Einsatzgruppe H in der Slowakei 1944/1945|title-link=Finale der Vernichtung |date=2013 |publisher=[[Wissenschaftliche Buchgesellschaft]] |location=Darmstadt |isbn=978-3-534-73733-8 |language=de|ref={{sfnref|\u0160indel\u00e1\u0159ov\u00e1|2013a}}}}\n: {{cite book |last1=Sniegon |first1=Tomas |title=Vanished History: The Holocaust in Czech and Slovak Historical Culture |date=2014 |publisher=[[Berghahn Books]] |isbn=978-1-78238-294-2 |language=en|location=New York|ref=harv|title-link=Vanished History: The Holocaust in Czech and Slovak Historical Culture }}\n:{{cite book |last=Sokolovi\u010d|first=Peter|title=Hlinkova Garda 1938 \u2013 1945|trans-title=Hlinka Guard 1938 \u2013 1945 |date=2013 |publisher=[[National Memory Institute (Slovakia)|National Memory Institute]]|location=Bratislava |isbn=978-80-89335-10-7 |url=https://www.upn.gov.sk/publikacie_web/hlinkova-garda.pdf|ref=harv|language=sk}}\n:{{cite book |last1=Ward |first1=James Mace |title=Priest, Politician, Collaborator: Jozef Tiso and the Making of Fascist Slovakia|title-link=Priest, Politician, Collaborator |date=2013|location=Ithaca |publisher=[[Cornell University Press]] |isbn=978-0-8014-6812-4 |language=en |ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Book chapters====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Bazyler |first1=Michael J.|authorlink=Michael Bazyler |last2=Boyd |first2=Kathryn Lee |last3=Nelson |first3=Kristen L. |last4=Shah |first4=Rajika L. |title=Searching for Justice after the Holocaust: Fulfilling the Terezin Declaration and Immovable Property Restitution |date=2019 |isbn=978-0-19-092306-8 |pages=401\u2013413 |ref={{sfnref|Bazyler et al.|2019}} |language=English |chapter=Slovakia|location=New York|publisher=Oxford University Press}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Dreyfus |first1=Jean-Marc|authorlink=Jean-Marc Dreyfus |last2=Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd |first2=Eduard|author2link=Eduard Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd  |editor1-last=Kosmala |editor1-first=Beate |editor2-last=Verbeeck |editor2-first=Georgi |title=Facing the Catastrophe: Jews and non-Jews in Europe during World War II |date=2011 |publisher=Berg |location=Oxford |isbn=978-1-84520-471-6 |language=en |chapter=Jews and non-Jews in the Aryanization Process: Comparison of France and the Slovak State, 1939\u201345|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite conference|last=Fatran|first=Gila|chapter=The Struggle for Jewish Survival during the Holocaust |pp=141\u2013162|editor1-last=D\u0142ugoborski|editor1-first=Wac\u0142aw|editor2-last=T\u00f3th |editor2-first=Dezider |editor3-last=Teresa|editor3-first=\u015awiebocka|editor4-last=Mensfelt|editor4-first=Jarek|translator-last=Mensfeld|translator-first=Jarek|title=The Tragedy of the Jews of Slovakia 1938\u20131945: Slovakia and the \"Final Solution of the Jewish Question\"|origyear=1992 |date =2002|publisher=[[Auschwitz-Birkenau State Museum]] and [[Museum of the Slovak National Uprising]]|location= O\u015bwi\u0119cim and Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica |language=en|ref=harv|isbn=978-83-88526-15-2}}\n*{{cite book|editor1-first=Jaroslava|editor1-last= Rogu\u013eov\u00e1|editor2-first= Maro\u0161 |editor2-last=Hertel  |last1=Hradsk\u00e1 |first1=Katar\u00edna |chapter=Dislok\u00e1cie \u017didov z Bratislavy na jese\u0148 1941 |title=Adepti Moci a \u00faspechu. Etablovanie El\u00edt V Modern\u00fdch Dejin\u00e1ch |date=2016 |pages=315\u2013324 |url=http://forumhistoriae.sk/documents/10180/1832590/bystricky-adepti-moci-a-uspechu.pdf#page=315 |trans-chapter=The Displacement of Jews from Bratislava in Autumn 1941|trans-title=Candidates for Power and Success. Formation of Elites in Modern History |language=sk |isbn=978-80-224-1503-3|ref=harv|publisher={{ill|Forum Historiae|sk}} ([[Slovak Academy of Sciences]])|location=Bratislava}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hutzelmann |first1=Barbara |editor1-last=Bajohr |editor1-first=Frank |editor2-last=L\u00f6w |editor2-first=Andrea |title=The Holocaust and European Societies: Social Processes and Social Dynamics |date=2016|location=London |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-1-137-56984-4 |pages=167\u2013185 |language=en |chapter=Slovak Society and the Jews: Attitudes and Patterns of Behaviour |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hutzelmann |first1=Barbara |editor1-last=Hutzelmann |editor1-first=Barbara|editor2-last=Hausleitner |editor2-first=Mariana |editor3-last=Hazan  |editor3-first=Souzana|title=Slowakei, Rum\u00e4nien und Bulgarien|trans-title=Slovakia, Romania, and Bulgaria |date=2018 |publisher=[[De Gruyter]] |location=Munich |isbn=978-3-11-049520-1 |language=de| series=[[Die Verfolgung und Ermordung der europ\u00e4ischen Juden durch das nationalsozialistische Deutschland 1933-1945]] [The Persecution and Murder of European Jews by Nazi Germany 1933-1945]|volume=13 |chapter=Einf\u00fchrung: Slowakei |trans-chapter=Introduction: Slovakia|ref=harv|pp=18\u201345}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Kamenec |first1=Ivan|chapter=The Slovak state, 1939\u20131945 |editor1-last=Teich |editor1-first=Mikul\u00e1\u0161 |editorlink=Mikul\u00e1\u0161 Teich|editor2-last=Kov\u00e1\u010d |editor2-first=Du\u0161an |editor2-link=Du\u0161an Kov\u00e1\u010d |editor3-last=Brown |editor3-first=Martin D. |title=Slovakia in History|title-link=Slovakia in History |date=2011 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |location=Cambridge |isbn=978-1-139-49494-6|language=en|doi=10.1017/CBO9780511780141|ref={{sfnref|Kamenec|2011a}}|pp=175\u2013192}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Kub\u00e1tov\u00e1 |first1=Hana |editor1-last=Henry |editor1-first=Patrick |title=Jewish Resistance Against the Nazis|title-link=Jewish Resistance Against the Nazis (book) |date=2014 |publisher=[[Catholic University of America Press]] |location=Washington, D.C. |isbn=978-0-8132-2589-0 |pages=504\u2013518 |ref=harv |language=en |chapter=Jewish Resistance in Slovakia, 1938\u20131945}}\n* {{cite book |first=Nina |last=Paulovi\u010dov\u00e1 |editor1-first = John-Paul |editor1-last = Himka |editor2-first = Joanna Beata |editor2-last =  Michlic |title=Bringing the Dark Past to Light. The Reception of the Holocaust in Postcommunist Europe.|title-link=Bringing the Dark Past to Light |chapter=The \"Unmasterable Past\"? The Reception of the Holocaust in Postcommunist Slovakia|location=Lincoln |publisher=University of Nebraska Press |year=2013 |isbn=978-0-8032-2544-2 |ref=harv |pp=549\u2013590}}\t\n*{{cite encyclopedia|entry=Slovakia|last1=Rothkirchen|first1=Livia |authorlink=Livia Rothkirchen|pp=595\u2013600 |editor1-last=Laqueur |editor1-first=Walter |editor-link=Walter Laqueur|editor2-last=Baumel |editor2-first=Judith Tydor |title=Holocaust Encyclopedia |date=2001 |publisher=Yale University Press |location=New Haven |language=en|isbn=978-0-300-08432-0|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=T\u00f6nsmeyer |first1=Tatjana|authorlink=Tatjana T\u00f6nsmeyer |editor1-last=Dean |editor1-first=Martin|editor1-link=Martin C. Dean |editor2-last=Goschler |editor2-first=Constantin |editor3-last=Ther |editor3-first=Philipp |title=Robbery and Restitution: The Conflict over Jewish Property in Europe |date=2007 |publisher=Berghahn Books |location=New York |isbn=9780857455642 |pages=81\u201396 |ref=harv |language=en |chapter=The Robbery of Jewish Property in Eastern European States Allied with Nazi Germany}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Book reviews====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Cichopek-Gajraj |first1=Anna |title=Nepokrade\u0161! N\u00e1lady a postoje slovensk\u00e9 spole\u010dnosti k \u017eidovsk\u00e9 ot\u00e1zce, 1938\u20131945 [Thou shall not steal! Moods and attitudes of Slovak society toward the Jewish question] |journal=East European Jewish Affairs |date=2018 |volume=48 |issue=2 |pages=253\u2013255 |doi=10.1080/13501674.2018.1505360|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Johnson |first1=Owen V. |title=\u017didovsk\u00e1 komunita na Slovensku medzi ceskoslovenskou parlamentnou demokraciou a slovensk\u00fdm \u0161t\u00e1tom v stredoeur\u00f3pskom kontexte, Eduard Ni\u017enansk\u00fd (Pre\u0161ov, Slovakia: Universum, 1999), 292 pp., 200 crowns (Slovak). |journal=Holocaust and Genocide Studies |date=2005 |volume=19 |issue=2 |pages=314\u2013317 |doi=10.1093/hgs/dci033|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Theses====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite thesis|degree=PhD|editor-last=Himka|editor-first=John-Paul|editor-link=John-Paul  Himka |last1=Paulovi\u010dov\u00e1 |first1=Nina |title=Rescue of Jews in the Slovak State (1939\u20131945) |date=2012 |url=https://era.library.ualberta.ca/items/e8340da1-7b46-40cc-95e1-d57665a23e34 |language=en|doi=10.7939/R33H33|institution=[[University of Alberta]]|ref=harv|location=Edmonton}}\n*{{cite thesis|last=Put\u00edk|first=Daniel|title=Sloven\u0161t\u00ed \u017did\u00e9 v Terez\u00edn\u011b, Sachsenhausenu, Ravensbr\u00fccku a Bergen-Belsenu, 1944/1945|language=cs|trans-title=Slovak Jews in Theresienstadt, Sachsenhausen, Ravensbr\u00fcck and Bergen-Belsen, 1944/1945|date=2015|degree=PhD|url=https://is.cuni.cz/webapps/zzp/detail/104422/?lang=en|institution=[[Charles University]]|location=Prague|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Journal articles====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=B\u00fcchler |first1=Yehoshua |title=The deportation of Slovakian Jews to the Lublin District of Poland in 1942 |journal=[[Holocaust and G