77/forhist.2019.13.1.7 |trans-title=No Man\u2019s Land in 1938. Deportation beyond the Bounds of Citizenship|language=sk |url=http://www.forumhistoriae.sk/en/clanok/no-mans-land-1938-deportation-beyond-bounds-citizenship|ref=harv}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Hallon |first1=\u013dudov\u00edt|title=Ariz\u00e1cia na Slovensku 1939\u20131945 |trans-title=Aryanization in Slovakia 1939\u20131945|url=https://www.vse.cz/polek/download.php?lang=en&jnl=aop&pdf=187.pdf |journal=Acta Oeconomica Pragensia |date=2007 |issue=7 |pages=148\u2013160|doi=10.18267/j.aop.187|language=cs|issn=1804-2112|ref=harv|volume=15}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Kamenec |first1=Ivan |title=Fenom\u00e9n korupcie v procese tzv. rie\u0161enia \"\u017eidovskej ot\u00e1zky\" na Slovensku v rokoch 1938\u20131945|trans-title=The phenomenon of corruption in the so-called solutions to the \"Jewish questions\" in Slovakia between 1938 and 1945 |pp=96\u2013112 |journal=Forum Historiae |date=2011 |volume=5 |issue=2 |url=http://www.forumhistoriae.sk/sk/clanok/fenomen-korupcie-v-procese-tzv-riesenia-zidovskej-otazky-na-slovensku-v-rokoch-1938-1945 |ref={{sfnref|Kamenec|2011b}} |language=sk |issn=1337-6861}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Kub\u00e1tov\u00e1 |first1=Hana |last2=L\u00e1n\u00ed\u010dek |first2=Jan |title=Jews and Gentiles in Central and Eastern Europe during the Holocaust in history and memory |journal=Holocaust Studies |date=2017|volume=23 |issue=1\u20132 |pages=1\u201316 |doi=10.1080/17504902.2016.1209838|ref=harv|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/310824429}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Legge |first1=Jerome S. |title=Collaboration, Intelligence, and the Holocaust: Ferdinand \u010eur\u010dansk\u00fd, Slovak Nationalism, and the Gehlen Organization |journal=Holocaust and Genocide Studies |date=2018 |volume=32 |issue=2 |pages=224\u2013248 |doi=10.1093/hgs/dcy029|ref=harv|issn=8756-6583}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=L\u00f4n\u010d\u00edkov\u00e1 |first1=Michala |title=Was the antisemitic propaganda a catalyst for tensions in the Slovak-Jewish relations? |journal=Holocaust Studies |date=2017 |volume=23 |issue=1\u20132 |pages=76\u201398 |doi=10.1080/17504902.2016.1209839 |ref=harv}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd |first1=Eduard |title=The discussions of Nazi Germany on the deportation of Jews in 1942 \u2013 the examples of Slovakia, Rumania and Hungary |url=http://www.historickycasopis.sk/pdf/HCsupplement2011.pdf|journal=Historick\u00fd \u010dasopis |date=2011 |volume=59 |issue=Supplement |pages=111\u2013136 |ref=harv |issn=0018-2575}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd |first1=Eduard |title=On Relations between the Slovak Majority and Jewish Minority During World War II |journal=[[Yad Vashem Studies]] |date=2014 |volume=42 |issue=2 |pages=47-90 |issn=0084-3296|ref=harv}}\n:{{cite journal |first=Nina |last1=Paulovi\u010dov\u00e1 |title=Holocaust Memory and Antisemitism in Slovakia: The Postwar Era to the Present |journal=[[Antisemitism Studies]]|publisher=Indiana University Press |date=2018 |volume=2 |issue=1 |pages=4\u201334|doi=10.2979/antistud.2.1.02|ref=harv}}\n:{{cite journal|last1=\u0160indel\u00e1\u0159ov\u00e1 |first1=Lenka |title=Einsatzgruppe H na povstaleck\u00e9m Slovensku (1944\u20131945) a pov\u00e1le\u010dn\u00e9 trestn\u00ed st\u00edh\u00e1n\u00ed|trans-title=Einsatzgruppe H in Uprising-era Slovakia (1944\u20131945) and Postwar Prosecution |url=http://www.usd.cas.cz/wp-content/uploads/sd_4_2013.pdf|issn=1210-7050|journal= [[:cs:Soudob\u00e9 d\u011bjiny (\u010dasopis)|Soudob\u00e9 d\u011bjiny]]|volume=XX|issue=4|date=2013 |language=cs|ref={{sfnref|\u0160indel\u00e1\u0159ov\u00e1|2013b}}|pp=582\u2013603}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Ward |first1=James Mace |title=\"People Who Deserve It\": Jozef Tiso and the Presidential Exemption |journal=Nationalities Papers |date=2002 |volume=30 |issue=4 |pages=571\u2013601 |doi=10.1080/00905992.2002.10540508|ref=harv|issn=1465-3923}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Ward |first1=James Mace |title=The 1938 