019 |work = [[The Hollywood Reporter]] | access-date = February 2, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | [[ADG Excellence in Production Design Award|Art Directors Guild Awards]]\n| [[Art Directors Guild Award for Excellence in Production Design for a Half Hour Single-Camera Television Series|Half-Hour Single-Camera Series]]\n| Michael Bricker <small>(for \"Nothing in This World Is Easy\")</small>\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/art-directors-guild-winners-2020-complete-list-1273722/item/period-film-art-directors-guild-award-winners-2020-1273734 |title='Parasite,' 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Win Art Directors Guild Awards |website=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Carolyn |last=Giardina |date=February 1, 2019 |accessdate=February 1, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" | [[Writers Guild of America Awards 2019|Writers Guild of America Awards]]\n| [[Writers Guild of America Award for Television: Comedy Series|Comedy Series]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Jocelyn Bioh]], Flora Birnbaum, Cirocco Dunlap, Leslye Headland, Natasha Lyonne, Amy Poehler, [[Tami Sagher]] & Allison Silverman\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/writers-guild-awards-2020-tv-nominations-1203426148/ |title=Writers Guild Unveils 2020 TV Award Nominees |first=Dave |last=McNary |date=December 5, 2019 |accessdate=December 5, 2019 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Writers Guild of America Award for Television: New Series|New Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | [[Nebula Award]]\n|[[Ray Bradbury Award|The Ray Bradbury Nebula Award for Outstanding Dramatic Presentation]]\n|Allison Silverman and Leslye Headland <small>(for \"The Way Out\")</small> \n|{{pending}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nebulas.sfwa.org/award-year/2020/|title=2019 - The Nebula Awards\u00ae|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Science Fiction & Fantasy Writers of America|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tor.com/2020/02/20/announcing-the-2019-nebula-awards-finalists/|title=Announcing the 2019 Nebula Awards Finalists|last=Tor.com|date=2020-02-20|website=Tor.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | [[Hugo Award]]\n|[[Hugo Award for Best Dramatic Presentation|Best Dramatic Presentation, Long Form]]\n|Natasha Lyonne, Leslye Headland, Amy Poehler, Jamie Babbit (for Season One)\n|{{pending}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Hugo Awards |url=http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/2020-hugo-awards/ |publisher=World Science Fiction Society |accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Netflix title|id=80211627}}\n* {{IMDb title|7520794}}\n\n{{Amy Poehler}}\n{{TCA Award for Outstanding New Program}}\n{{Netflix original current series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Russian Doll (TV series)}}\n[[Category:2010s American comedy-drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American mystery television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American time travel television series]]\n[[Category:2019 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:American science fiction web series]]\n[[Category:Comedy-drama web series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Fiction about memory erasure and alteration]]\n[[Category:Television series about Jews and Judaism]]\n[[Category:Mystery web series]]\n[[Category:Netflix original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series about parallel universes]]\n[[Category:Television series by 3 Arts Entertainment]]\n[[Category:Television series by Paper Kite Productions]]\n[[Category:Television series by Universal Television]]\n[[Category:Television shows about death]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in New York City]]\n[[Category:Time loop television series]]\n", "name_user": "Drovethrughosts", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAccolades", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Doll_(TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "Hareem Shah", "text_new": "{{short description|Pakistani TikToker}}\n{{Infobox biography\n| name = Hareem Shah\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| birth_date = \n| death_date =\n| citizenship = Pakistani\n| birth_place = [[Peshawar]], [[Pakistan]]\n| party =  \n| children = \n| occupation = [[Social media star]]\n| organization  = \n| years_active  = 2018\u2013present\n| website = \n| alma_mater = \n\nIs the beat friend of Akhtar Bhai Ras Al Khaimah Toyota Previa walay.\n\n}}\n'''Fiza Hussain''', known by her [[stage name]] '''Hareem Shah''', is a Pakistani social media star who became famous from her videos on [[TikTok]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/world/story/tiktok-star-hareem-shah-video-sheikh-rasheed-ahmad-imran-khan-pakistan-1633398-2020-01-02|title=Hareem Shah: TikTok star sex scandal leaves Imran Khan government red-faced|first1=Ganesh Radha-Udayakumar New|last1=DelhiJanuary 2|first2=2020UPDATED:|last2=January 2|first3=2020 19:40|last3=Ist|website=India Today}}</ref> She plans to leave Pakistan and has applied for emigration to Canada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.urdupoint.com/en/pakistan/tiktok-girl-hareem-shah-decides-to-leave-paki-799178.html|title=Tiktok Girl Hareem Shah Decides To Leave Pakistan|website=UrduPoint}}</ref>She is only famous because of her blunt and seductive actions in her videos and getting limelight from defaming politicians and anchors \n\nBorn to Zarar Hussain Shah, she was born as Fiza Hussain and studied at religious school.<ref>https://tribune.com.pk/story/2129271/1-aalma-tiktok-star-hareem-shahs-father-seeks-apology-controversial-videos/</ref> She is a student of Masters of Philosophy in Competitive Religion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/lifestyle/celebrity/story/who-is-hareem-shah-the-pak-tiktok-star-viral-for-her-imran-khan-connection-1633404-2020-01-02|title=Who is Hareem Shah, the Pak TikTok star viral for her Imran Khan connection?|first1=Nishtha Grover New|last1=DelhiJanuary 2|